[1
Date: Tue 23 Jan 2001 16:10:15 -0500
From: ProMED-mail <promed@promedmail.org>
Source: News Ltd. Australia [edited

France reported 4 new cases of mad cow disease, including the first detected
under a testing scheme for all cattle aged over 30 months destined for the
food chain. The first case found by the testing program, which the French
Government launched earlier this month, involved an animal born in 1995 in
the Ain region of eastern France. The findings brought to 10 the total
number of cases of mad cow disease, or bovine spongiform encephalopathy,
found this year in France. A total of 162 cases were found in 2000.
